description._content: View near Cascades Landing Place, Anson Bay. "The scenery is exceedingly beautiful, and in an attempt to describe its particular type of beauty, the epithet "pearl-like" seems to come spontaneously to everyone's thoughts." - Norfolk Island (Historical and Descriptive) Lantern Lecture by Frank Walker, RAHS, 1917. This image is part of a collection entitled 'Views of Norfolk Island', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
